-- With the landed DedekindBridge.lo<œÜ (‚àÉn, q<lo n ‚üπ q ‚àà œÜL) this makes œÜL q ‚ü∫ ‚àÉn, q < lo n ‚Äî the two
-- œÜ's (the Dedekind point and the running corridor) have the SAME cut.  Engine: the Cassini gap 1/D¬≤
-- (GapBound) ‚Üí 0 (recip‚Üí0, via Forcing's unbounded denominators + ‚Ñö-archimedean), so f(lo n) = lo n¬≤‚àí
-- lo n = 1 ‚àí 1/D¬≤ climbs past f(q) for any q below œÜ, and quad-squeeze (the order-reflection through
-- f(x)=x¬≤‚àíx) turns that into q < lo n.  No new analysis ‚Äî the corridor IS the point.
--
